The paper discusses the capacity of TV white space networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of propagation models and trade-offs between network capacity and system parameters, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses incumbent protection rules and interference from TV transmitters, which are topics related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) and computer networks and communications (cs.COM).
